	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />Yes, there is enough information in those 8 samples per pixel to exactly calculate the 9-bit hue/luminosity/emphasis was intended. However, figuring out when to sample either involves a fairly sophisticated PLL (12Ã—, only 10 periods of fundamental to sample, to recover subpixel phase), a 150MHz ADC, or access to both the PPU's VIDEO_OUT and 22MHz signals, the latter of which is not available except by soldering inside.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


